Patch Set 3:

I have drafted another workaround to fix this issue, but it looks not safe to expose sql string in the code, 

@zhiyan , @feilong , also need your opinions on this method, thanks.

def upgrade(migrate_engine):
    meta = sqlalchemy.schema.MetaData(migrate_engine)
    image_locations = Table('image_locations', meta, autoload=True)

    session = orm.sessionmaker(bind=migrate_engine)()

    sql_str = text("select il.id from image_locations il where \
                il.id>(select min(id) from image_locations  \
                where image_id=il.image_id and value=il.value \
                and meta_data=il.meta_data) and (select count(*) \
                from image_locations where image_id=il.image_id \
                and value=il.value and meta_data=il.meta_data)>1")
    qry = session.execute(sql_str)

    for row in qry:
        stmt =(image_locations.delete()
               .where(image_locations.c.id == row[0])
               .where(image_locations.c.deleted == False))
        stmt.execute()

    session.close()
